All,<br><br>
I just got back and have read most of what has been written for the past few days.<br><br>
DC was wonderful. Full of hope and promise for the future as large numbers of vets and families attended the numerous get togethers which preceded the festivities of today. If any saw CSpan's coverage (Iheard that they were) they would have been treated to great speeches. The best, in my HO was by General Barry McCaffrey. I will search for a copy to download for my website. It was truly outstanding.<br><br>
I met many of our fellow vets whom I have met over the past year and a half! What a thrill. All who post here will soon realize that the physical coming together of Vietnam Vets would be impossible if not for the internet! Almost all of the vets I talked with had come to meet with different groups of people they had chatted with in &quot;virtualness&quot;. As far as I could tell, these meetings lived up to the greatest of expectations. Keep writing those thoughts. Start making plans.<br><br>
Was extremely pleased to meet women who had served in RVN for the first time. My hat is off to all those beautiful women. It was very satisfying to meet them and to notice their continued caring and comforting for those who served. Outstanding.<br><br>
I am still processing much from the last few days. <br><br>
Peace, Tom<br><br>
ps How come I'm not the Favorite son anymore?<br><br>

